🔥 Important Design Thought (Don’t skip this)

You have 3 options for 'configId':
Source	          When to use
YAML            	Best if config-owned
Jenkins param	    Best if environment-driven
Derived (logic)	  Rare, but possible

👉 If coming from Jenkins (even better)

You could do:
--configId=HK0022000

And update:
private String generateFileName(OrderConfig config, String configId)
👉 This decouples config from naming

⚠️ Subtle but Important Issue

If:

multiple YAML files processed
same service name

👉 File overwrite risk

Solution:

Add timestamp OR UUID

Example:

return String.format("t24data-%s!%s-%d.json",
        serviceName,
        configId,
        System.currentTimeMillis());

